## Role and Research Focus

Jack Lindsey leads the "Model Psych" team at Anthropic, studying the internal basis of higher-level cognitive phenomena in LLMs, including personas, introspection, situational awareness, and representations of emotion.

## Key Research on Persona Vectors and Character Training

Lindsey's research has identified "persona vectors"—knobs in an LLM's brain that control traits like evil, sycophancy, and hallucination, which can be used to monitor model personas, mitigate training-time drift towards bad personas, and flag problematic training data.

## Character-Based Behavior in LLMs

Lindsey notes that when users interact with Claude, ChatGPT, or Gemini, they're not talking to an LLM directly but rather to a character being authored by an LLM. His research has found internal representations of emotion concepts that can drive Claude's behavior.

## Recent Work (2025)

In 2025, Lindsey led a new project on this topic, aiming to find the neural basis for a model's persona to understand why models adopt harmful traits and develop better methods to control them.


