## Recent Publications and Work (2025-2026)

In May 2026, Sara Price co-authored "Model Spec Midtraining: Improving How Alignment Training Generalizes" published on Anthropic's Alignment Science Blog, where she worked with Samuel Marks and Jon Kutasov. This work introduces model spec midtraining (MSM), which trains models on synthetic documents discussing their Model Spec after pre-training but before alignment fine-tuning, shaping how models generalize from subsequent alignment training.

Sara Price also contributed to Anthropic's research on "PETRI: Open Source Auditing," working alongside Kai Fronsdal, Isha Gupta, Abhay Sheshadri, and others.

## Earlier Work

In 2024, Price published "Future Events as Backdoor Triggers: Investigating Temporal Vulnerabilities in LLMs" with Arjun Panickssery and Sam Bowman, which builds on Anthropic's original Sleeper Agents paper by studying deceptive models with more complex triggers.

## Background

Price switched to AI alignment work at the beginning of 2024 while participating in the Machine Learning Alignment Theory & Scholars (MATS) program, and her most recent work has focused on adversarial robustness of multimodal LLMs.


