# Article Summary

**Title:** Model Spec Midtraining: Improving How Alignment Training Generalizes

**Authors:** Chloe Li (Anthropic Fellows Program), Sara Price, Samuel Marks, Jon Kutasov (Anthropic)

**Abstract:**
The researchers introduce model spec midtraining (MSM), a technique implemented between pretraining and fine-tuning phases. During this intermediate stage, models train on synthetic documents discussing their Model Spec. This approach shapes how models generalize from subsequent alignment training, enabling models with identical fine-tuning to adopt different values depending on their MSM specifications.

**Key Themes:**
- Improving alignment generalization through intermediate training on Model Spec content
- Reducing agentic misalignment in deployed LLM agents
- Empirical study of Model Spec properties affecting alignment
- Comparison of rules-based versus values-based specification approaches
- Token efficiency gains in alignment fine-tuning

**Co-Authors:**
Sara Price, Samuel Marks, Jon Kutasov

