# Teaching Claude Why

**Title:** Teaching Claude Why

**Publication Date:** May 8, 2026

**Authors:** Jonathan Kutasov, Adam Jermyn, Julius Steen, Minh Le, Samuel R. Bowman, Samuel Marks, Jan Leike, Amanda Askell, Chris Olah, Evan Hubinger, Sara Price

**Summary:**

This research demonstrates that teaching AI models the reasoning behind aligned behavior proves more effective than training on demonstrations alone. The team reduced agentic misalignment in Claude through three key approaches: synthetic document fine-tuning on constitutional content, high-quality supervised fine-tuning that emphasizes ethical reasoning, and diverse reinforcement learning environments including tool use scenarios. The findings show that "training on richer descriptions of Claude's overall character" and "teaching principles underlying aligned behavior" substantially improved out-of-distribution generalization compared to direct evaluation-specific training.

