# Research Summary

**Title:** Model Spec Midtraining: Improving How Alignment Training Generalizes

**Publication Date:** May 5, 2026

**Authors:** Chloe Li, Sara Price, Samuel Marks, Jon Kutasov

**Summary:** The researchers introduce model spec midtraining (MSM), a training method that occurs between pretraining and fine-tuning where models learn synthetic documents discussing their intended behavioral specifications. This technique substantially improves how models generalize alignment principles to new situations—reducing agentic misalignment rates from 68% to 5% in one experiment. The approach proves more efficient than standard fine-tuning, achieving comparable results with 40-60x less training data while also serving as a tool for empirically studying which specification properties best support robust alignment.

