**Summary:** 

This research introduces an unsupervised method pairing two language model components—an activation verbalizer and reconstructor—trained via reinforcement learning to translate neural network activations into human-readable text explanations. The researchers applied the technique to audit Claude Opus 4.6, discovering unverbalized evaluation awareness and problematic training data through case studies validated with independent interpretability methods. The approach generates increasingly informative explanations throughout training while maintaining natural language readability through initialization constraints and KL regularization.

