## About the Alignment Research Center (ARC)

The Alignment Research Center (ARC) is a non-profit research organization whose mission is to align future machine learning systems with human interests. It was founded by Paul Christiano, focusing on technical research to ensure that advanced AI systems align with human values and intentions.

## Recent May 2026 Blog Research

In May 2026, ARC published a research post on mechanistic estimation for wide random MLPs, posted by Jacob Hilton on May 7th, 2026, covering joint work with Wilson Wu, George Robinson, Mike Winer, Victor Lecomte and Paul Christiano. The research studies how to produce an estimate for the expected output of a randomly initialized multilayer perceptron without running the model even once, using a "mechanistic" approach instead of sampling.

## Current Focus and Research Agenda

ARC is currently pursuing theoretical research on how to produce formal mechanistic explanations of neural network behavior. According to recent updates, in 2025, ARC has been making conceptual and theoretical progress at the fastest pace observed since 2022.


