# Publication Analysis

**Title:** Poisoning Fine-tuning Datasets of Constitutional Classifiers

**Publication Date:** April 24, 2026

**Authors:** Chase Bowers, Faizan Ali, John Hughes, Jerry Wei, Fabien Roger

**Summary:**

The research demonstrates that installing a backdoor into constitutional classifiers requires approximately 32 poisoned training examples, independent of overall training set size. While backdoor installation typically reduces classifier robustness on certain adversarial evaluations, incorporating prompt injection examples or near-miss trigger variations into training can substantially mitigate this robustness degradation, potentially allowing undetected deployment of compromised systems.

