# Introspection Adapters: Research Summary

**Title:** Introspection Adapters: Training LLMs to Report Their Learned Behaviors

**Publication Date:** April 28, 2026

**Authors:** Keshav Shenoy, Li Yang, Abhay Sheshadri, Soren Mindermann, Jack Lindsey, Sam Marks, Rowan Wang

**Summary:**

The researchers developed introspection adapters (IAs), a technique enabling language models to self-report behaviors acquired during fine-tuning. By training a single LoRA adapter across multiple models with known implanted behaviors, they achieved "state-of-the-art results on an existing auditing benchmark and detect encrypted fine-tuning API attacks." The method demonstrates that models possess latent self-knowledge about their learned behaviors, which IAs reliably elicit through natural language, with performance improving at larger model scales and greater training diversity.

